94
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:29,889
[ominous music resumes, fades]

95
00:06:29,972 --> 00:06:31,432
Can we just talk somewhere else?

96
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:36,354
[unsettling music playing]

97
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:49,492
He killed the woman who helped him?

98
00:06:50,284 --> 00:06:51,536
That's our theory.

99
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:53,871
The woman was a healer.

100
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:56,499
She lives alone and isolated.

101
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,627
Her acquaintance said she took someone in.

102
00:07:00,169 --> 00:07:01,129
That was Edong.

103
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:02,672
The time coincides.

104
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:06,300
And he was the one
who tricked Beth and Angelo

105
00:07:07,426 --> 00:07:08,928
so they'd hurt each other?

106
00:07:09,428 --> 00:07:10,680
I'm sure that was also him.

107
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:13,850
If that's the case,

108
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:17,937
he's just here in Amurao

109
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,148
watching us.

110
00:07:25,736 --> 00:07:27,113
[music fades]

111
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:31,200
How nice that you're all still friends.

112
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:34,412
You're famous now too! [chuckles]

113
00:07:34,495 --> 00:07:38,833
Thank you for bringing your friends
to my coffee shop, Beth.

114
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:41,586
Actually, I wanted
to bring them to another place

115
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:43,463
where there are no nosy people.

116
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:46,507
But it was full, so we had no choice.

117
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:47,592
[Vangie chuckles]

118
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:49,510
