119
00:07:49,594 --> 00:07:51,679
Enjoy your drinks. [chuckles]

120
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:53,055
They're good.

121
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:55,224
[uneasy music playing]

122
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:56,517
Enjoy.

123
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,103
Go on, try it.

124
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:04,692
Oh, I'll excuse myself now. Enjoy.

125
00:08:06,194 --> 00:08:07,570
[music fades]

126
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:10,281
I'm warning you, lower your voices.

127
00:08:10,781 --> 00:08:12,825
She's the number
one gossip here in Amurao.

128
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,332
Sorry, guys.

129
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,502
I can't offer my place.

130
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:26,047
I haven't told Scott yet about Edong.

131
00:08:26,130 --> 00:08:28,633
I honestly thought
I didn't have to because…

132
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:30,092
he's, he's dead.

133
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,844
- Right?
- [Erica] Alice.

134
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:33,679
Alice, tell him now.

135
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:38,601
All of you should tell your family.

136
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,394
Edong's more violent now.

137
00:08:41,145 --> 00:08:44,649
I don't know what he'll do next or who…

138
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:46,651
his next target is.

139
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,238
But the police are looking for him, right?

140
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,491
If they found him once,
they can find him again.

141
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:56,911
The police are still
hesitating to believe Lucas.

142
00:08:57,370 --> 00:09:00,873
And the only person
who saw him is Ayoc's wife.

143
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:02,959
But she doesn't want to talk.

144
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:06,128
Tch. Does my family
have to go through this again?

145
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,922
What else does that bastard want?

146
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:10,174
Hasn't he done enough?

147
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:12,134
Does he want us to invent a time machine

148
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:14,845
so he doesn't go to jail 14 years ago?

149
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:17,723
[unsettling music playing]

150
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:19,809
[Edong] <i>Have you been sleeping well</i>

151
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:24,480
<i>the past 14 years</i>
<i>after what you did to me?</i>

152
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:27,316
<i>You lied.</i>

153
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:30,319
<i>And because of that,</i>
<i>I was imprisoned in here.</i>

154
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:34,198
- There's something else we can do.
- [music fades]

155
00:09:35,032 --> 00:09:36,492
Tell the truth.

156
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:41,247
[tense music playing]

157
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:42,498
Let's face him.

158
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:44,083
Let's face everyone.

159
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:45,793
Let's tell them the truth.

160
00:09:46,961 --> 00:09:49,213
Let's tell them
we our statements were wrong,

161
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:51,674
and it's the reason Edong went to jail.

162
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:56,554
[tense music continues]

163
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:59,140
It's the root cause of all this, right?

164
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:02,184
He knows we wronged him.

165
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:06,480
Including Amurao, the police, the law.

166
00:10:07,231 --> 00:10:09,358
He feels like everyone ganged up on him.

167
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:12,153
If we admit that we lied, he might--

168
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:13,654
I'm not going to admit anything!

169
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:15,823
We did the right thing
for Louisa, remember?!

170
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:19,702
Why can't you admit it even now, Beth?

171
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:21,787
Stop using Louisa as an excuse.

172
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:23,914
We made a mistake, and that's the truth!

173
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:27,335
What you really want
to say is I made a mistake. Right?

174
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:29,253
I said it clearly. Us.

175
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:31,756
Really, Erica?

176
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:33,633
Ever since we met again,

177
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:36,677
you've been implying that it was my fault!

178
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,387
It was all our fault!

179
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:42,016
You think I don't regret everyday
that I didn't speak up back then?

180
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:46,687
[tense music continues]

181
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:48,481
I won't do it.

182
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:55,321
You may have nothing to lose, but I do.

183
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:58,032
Oh, that's right,

184
00:10:58,115 --> 00:11:02,119
You're my successful friend
who always gives TV interviews!

185
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,913
What the fuck, Beth?!

186
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:05,956
I already apologized to you, right?

187
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,376
You can be so damn petty sometimes.

188
00:11:08,459 --> 00:11:11,003
Guys, please, just stop!

189
00:11:12,588 --> 00:11:16,008
Can we just calm down, please?!

190
00:11:19,303 --> 00:11:24,475
[phone buzzing]

191
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:35,569
[phone buzzing]

192
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:43,577
[unsettling music playing]

193
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:54,922
I'll just use the restroom.

194
00:11:58,551 --> 00:11:59,552
[Erica sighs]

195
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:08,310
So you blatantly hurt other women now too.

196
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:09,520
[Anton] <i>So…</i>

197
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:11,230
you've talked to your spy?

198
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:12,898
Yes.

199
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:15,693
And she's going
to report you to the police.

200
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:17,361
You think I'm scared?

201
00:12:18,946 --> 00:12:21,490
She can be bought like everyone else.

202
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:22,700
[scoffs]

203
00:12:23,451 --> 00:12:24,869
You don't know her, Anton.

204
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:26,454
[scoffs]

205
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:29,039
Where are you now?

206
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:31,375
At Alice's.

207
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:32,918
Where else?

208
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:35,087
<i>You probably excused</i>
<i>yourself from your friends</i>

209
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:37,840
because you don't want
them to hear us fighting, right?

210
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:39,341
[scoffs]

211
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:43,012
<i>That is why we're a team, Mel.</i>

212
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,890
You want this marriage to last.

213
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:48,726
You want to protect me.

214
00:12:49,727 --> 00:12:51,395
<i>You'd even stand next to a trash can</i>

215
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:53,939
<i>just so I wouldn't look</i>
<i>bad in front of your friends.</i>

216
00:12:54,523 --> 00:12:56,192
[chuckles]

217
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:58,235
You're so predictable.

218
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:01,906
Excuse me. I'm not doing this for you.

219
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:06,035
[foreboding music playing]

220
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:07,203
Wait.

221
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:10,289
What did you just say?

222
00:13:11,415 --> 00:13:12,416
I said…

223
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:15,628
you'd even answer my call

224
00:13:15,711 --> 00:13:19,298
<i>next to a trash can just to protect me.</i>

225
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:23,677
[foreboding music continues]

226
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:41,987
[foreboding music intensifies]

227
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:53,666
What are you doing here?

228
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:56,919
Let's go.

229
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:59,046
- Let's go home.
- Let me go!

230
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:03,217
Why don't you scream?

231
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:05,219
Go ahead and scream.

232
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:07,972
So that your friends
will find out the truth.

233
00:14:08,847 --> 00:14:09,807
You can't do it, right?

234
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:12,851
- Let's go!
- [grunts]

235
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:14,270
[both grunting]

236
00:14:15,062 --> 00:14:16,146
- [grunts]
- [blow lands]

237
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,606
[groans]

238
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:22,403
[dramatic music playing]

239
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:23,487
[Anton grunts]

240
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,366
You let another man touch you?!

241
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:31,912
What are you talking about?!

242
00:14:31,996 --> 00:14:33,998
